<paragraph id="8B8236C7FFB2FF98FFEAF94E69EDF873" blockId="48.[151,1437,1621,2044]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB2FF98FFEAF94E69C9F93F" bold="true" box="[199,443,1765,1791]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Revised description.</emphasis>
Only tiny, juvenile shells comprising three teleoconch whorls available. Small slender fusiform with high spire; apical angle ~30°. Protoconch high, turreted, paucispiral with strongly convex initial part and weakly convex last whorl. First teleoconch whorl weakly convex with indistinct subsutural spiral cord. Commashaped riblets crossed by weak spiral cords on later teleoconch whorls resulting in beaded appearance. Whorl profile slightly angulated at mid-whorl. Last preserved whorl with slightly protruding weakly beaded shoulder. Base low, moderately constricted.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C327654CFFB2FF99FFEAF8166BD5FEDC" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8236C7FFB2FF99FFEAF8166B74FF39" blockId="48.[151,1437,1621,2044]" lastBlockId="49.[151,1437,151,357]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB2FF98FFEAF816693EF817" bold="true" box="[199,332,1981,2007]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Discussion.</emphasis>
The status of this species is unclear as only juvenile specimens are known. Its early whorl sculpture differs from other Sarmatian species such as 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB2FF98FDA3F84A6C75F83C" authority="(Hornes, 1854)" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Hornes" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[654,1031,2017,2044]" class="Insecta" family="Phylloxeridae" genus="Olegia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="doderleini">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB2FF98FDA3F84A6B26F83B" box="[654,852,2017,2043]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Olegia doderleini</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB2FF98FC4EF84A6B8DF83C" author="Hornes, M." box="[867,1023,2017,2044]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="297 - 382" refId="ref135553" refString="Hornes, M. (1854) Die fossilen Mollusken des Tertiar-Beckens von Wien. Abhandlungen der K. K. Geologischen Reichsanstalt, 3, 297 - 382, pls. XXXIII - XL (1854). [https: // opac. geologie. ac. at / ais 312 / dokumente / Abh- 3 - GRA-gesamt. pdf]" type="journal article" year="1854">Hörnes, 1854</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB2FF98FB3EF84A6CFDF83B" authority="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen, 2022" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1043,1167,2017,2043]" class="Insecta" family="Phylloxeridae" genus="Olegia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandici" status="nov. sp.">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB2FF98FB3EF84A6CFDF83B" box="[1043,1167,2017,2043]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">O. mandici</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A57AEFFB2FF98FBBBF84A6C9FF83B" box="[1174,1261,2017,2043]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" rank="species">nov. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB2FF99FA0EF84A699AFF71" authority="(Simionescu &amp; Barbu, 1940)" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Simionescu &amp; Barbu" baseAuthorityYear="1940" class="Insecta" family="Phylloxeridae" genus="Olegia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" order="Hemiptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rumana">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB2FF98FA0EF84A6DEEF83B" box="[1315,1436,2017,2043]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">O. rumana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FFB2FF3C6992FF71" author="Simionescu, I. &amp; Barbu, I. Z." box="[159,480,151,177]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 194" refId="ref144291" refString="Simionescu, I. &amp; Barbu, I. Z. (1940) La faune sarmatienne de Roumanie. Memoriile Institutului Geologic al Romaniei, 3, 1 - 194, 11 pls." type="journal article" year="1940">Simionescu &amp; Barbu, 1940</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The beads on the axial riblets on early teleoconch whorls are reminiscent of the Sarmatian 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D44FFB3FF99FE22FF106A67FF15" authority="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen, 2022" authorityName="Harzhauser &amp; Landau &amp; Janssen" authorityYear="2022" box="[271,533,187,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Clavatulidae" genus="Granulatocincta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="callim" status="nov. sp.">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FE22FF106A67FF15" box="[271,533,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Granulatocincta callim</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A57AEFFB3FF99FD36FF106A01FF15" box="[539,627,187,213]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" rank="species">nov. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but the latter develops well-defined beads at the abapical suture at same growth stage and a central spiral cord of delicate beads.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236C7FFB3FF99FFEAFEA96BD5FEDC" blockId="49.[151,1437,151,357]" box="[199,935,258,285]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FFEAFEA969DAFEDC" bold="true" box="[199,424,258,284]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Paleoenvironment.</emphasis>
Coastal inner neritic (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B36FFB3FF99FD8DFEA86BEAFEDD" author="Lukeneder, S. &amp; Zuschin, M. &amp; Harzhauser, M. &amp; Mandic, O." box="[672,920,259,285]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="767 - 784" refId="ref138028" refString="Lukeneder, S., Zuschin, M., Harzhauser, M. &amp; Mandic, O. (2011) Spatiotemporal signals and palaeoenvironments of endemic molluscan assemblages in the marine system of the Sarmatian Paratethys. Acta Palaeontologica Polonica, 56, 767 - 784. [https: // www. app. pan. pl / archive / published / app 56 / app 20100046. pdf] https: // doi. org / 10.4202 / app. 2010.0046" type="journal article" year="2011">
Lukeneder 
<emphasis id="B949EAD5FFB3FF99FC0DFEA86B2BFEDD" box="[800,857,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
